title: Grateful Dead Live at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium on 1973-06-09
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Deal, Looks Like Rain, They Love Each Other, Jack Straw, Loose Lucy, Mexicali Blues, Row Jimmy, El Paso, Box Of Rain, Sugaree, Beat It On Down The Line, Tennessee Jed, Greatest Story Ever Told, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Playin' In The Band, Loser, Me & My Uncle, Mississippi Half Step, Big River, Eyes Of The World-> China Doll, Sugar Magnolia

Sound check: China Cat->I Know You Rider. Do

reviews.review_text: Fantastic Big gratitude to Monte Barry, tons of work to make this matrix. And one of the very great shows.

- Splendid matrix, although the juxtaposition of the snappy SBD and the echo from the delay towers is slightly too weird at times. Has to be one of the Dead's all-time greatest shows. Phil's lead vocal on Box is jaw-dropping, as is the Truckin' jam and lots of other bits, and when you're not gaping in disbelief you'll be boogiein'. Slight set list error in description: set 1 ends with Tennessee Jed, not 3 songs later.
